title: Bug 49235: ServletContainerInitializer onStartup(Set<Class<? classSet is not expected class
description: Bug 49235: ServletContainerInitializer onStartup(Set<Class<? The output is "MySomeClass".
OB: The output of the code snippet provided is "MySomeAnn" instead of "MySomeClass".
SR:
To reproduce the issue: 
1. Build Tomcat 7.0.0 from svn r939221. 
2. Run the code snippet provided: 
   - Ensure that the class "MySomeClass" is annotated with "@MySomeAnn". 
   - Implement the "ModuleInitializer" class and override the "onStartup" method. 
   - Pass "classSet" as a parameter to the "onStartup" method. 
3. Observe the output, which should be "MySomeClass".
